# Build-context hygiene. Keep this list broad — everything that enters the
# `docker build` context can land in builder-stage layers or the build cache,
# which is leakable via `--target server` or `docker buildx build --cache-to`.
# Anything remotely secret MUST be listed here (secrets stay as RUNTIME env,
# never build args). See gaka-o5k for the full rationale.

# ── VCS / build outputs ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.git
tmp/
bin/
.dolt/
*.db

# ── env & credentials ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .envrc (direnv), .env and every .env.* variant, plus assorted local key/state
# files. We whitelist .env.example so the runtime image documentation is available
# in the build context if ever needed (nothing in the current build uses it).
.envrc
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.local.json
.beads-credential-key

# ── agent / tooling state (may contain local settings, tokens, prompts) ─────
.claude/
.serena/
.agents/
.codex/
.playwright-mcp/
.beads/

# ── Node / frontend intermediates (rebuilt in the multi-stage image) ────────
web/node_modules/
web/dist/
web/.vite/
web/coverage/

# ── Embedded SPA output (rebuilt in the multi-stage image) ──────────────────
internal/server/dist/

# ── Bloat / non-code (never needed at build time) ───────────────────────────
.github/
docs/
*.png
*.md
# CHANGELOG.md is embedded via //go:embed — keep it in the context.
!CHANGELOG.md
ov.md
.air.toml
docker-compose*.yml
Dockerfile*
Taskfile.yml
.travis.yml
default.nix
release.nix
shell.nix

# ── Editor / OS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp

# ── Playwright verification artifacts ───────────────────────────────────────
/*-council-*.png
/overview-*.png
/projects-*.png
/audit-*.png
/fixed-*.png

# ── Stray built binaries ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
/fixturegen
/boomtime
